Class KafkaDeserializerExtractor

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Instrumentable, Extractor<Object,Object>, FinalState, Closeable, AutoCloseable

    @Alias(value="DESERIALIZER")
public class KafkaDeserializerExtractor
extends KafkaExtractor<Object,Object>

    Extension of KafkaExtractor that wraps Kafka's Deserializer API. Kafka's Deserializer provides a generic way of converting Kafka Messages to Object. Typically, a Deserializer will be used along with a Serializer which is responsible for converting an Object to a Kafka Message. These APIs are useful for reading and writing to Kafka, since Kafka is primarily a byte oriented system.

    This class wraps the Deserializer API allowing any existing classes that implement the Deserializer API to integrate with seamlessly with Gobblin. The deserializer can be specified in the following ways:

    • KAFKA_DESERIALIZER_TYPE can be used to specify a pre-defined enum from KafkaDeserializerExtractor.Deserializers or it can be used to specify the fully-qualified name of a Class that defines the Deserializer interface. If this property is set to a class name, then KafkaSchemaRegistry must also be specified using the KafkaSchemaRegistry.KAFKA_SCHEMA_REGISTRY_CLASS config key
